  "pid": "rylJwpXCME",
  "programNotes": "<h4>Program notes</h4> <ul> <li>In choosing electives, it is recommended that students consider the prerequisite requirements for PHYS or EOS courses in Year 4.</li> <li>Most 400-level EOS classes are offered in alternate years. A schedule of when each class is offered is available on the School of Earth and Ocean Sciences website.</li> <li>One of <a href=\"#/courses/r1xamu6m4\">EOS 427</a> or <a href=\"#/courses/rks50O6XE\">PHYS 427</a> is required in the program, and may be taken in either third of fourth year.</li> <li><a href=\"#/courses/H1ei0OaXN\">PHYS 460A</a> and <a href=\"#/courses/rkexiRuTQ4\">460B</a> are recommended for third- and fourth-year students.</li> </ul>",
